data.title: The 65+ Best Family Channel Shows, Ranked
data.meta_description: Over 500 TV viewers have voted on the 65+ Best Family Channel Shows, Ranked. Current Top 3: Life with Derek, Franklin, The Next Step
data.text:
Ranked By

4.6K votes

516 voters

Voting Rules

Vote up the best original TV shows that have ever debuted on The Family Channel.

Family Channel TV shows have always had a special place in our hearts, providing quality entertainment for the whole family to enjoy. These shows are known for their engaging storylines, lovable characters, and the valuable life lessons they teach viewers of all ages. These shows have been voted on and curated by fans, not stuffy critics. They are regarded as some of the best family-friendly content ever created on television.

Throughout the years, Family Channel has introduced us to an array of unforgettable programs that cater to different tastes and interests. Some prime examples include Life With Derek, a comedic series about a blended family trying to navigate their new life together, Franklin, an endearing animated show that follows the adventures of a young turtle and his friends, and The Next Step, which showcases the journey of talented dancers striving for success at an elite dance studio. Each of these shows offers something unique, capturing the hearts of millions around the world.

Now it's your turn to weigh in on which Family Channel TV shows are truly the best. By casting your vote, you'll help determine which programs stand out among the rest as fan favorites. So sit back, reminisce on those cherished memories, and let your voice be heard in this crowd-ranked list celebrating The Best Family Channel TV Shows.

Most divisive: The Latest Buzz

Over 500 Ranker voters have come together to rank this list of The 65+ Best Family Channel Shows, Ranked

1

Life with Derek

Michael Seater, Ashley Leggat, Jordan Todosey

Premiered : 2005

Blending humor, quirkiness, and family values together, this witty series showcases an unusual yet relatable dynamic between step-siblings. When their two families merge into one household – hilarity ensues! Navigating through the often chaotic teenage years and learning to live in harmony as siblings, these kids provide laughter and heartwarming moments for viewers of all ages. With its well-crafted characters and engaging storylines, it's no wonder this show has left a lasting impression on many viewers' hearts.

Life with Derek is a Canadian television sitcom that aired on Family and VRAK.TV in Canada and on Disney Channel in the United States. The series premiered on Family on September 18, 2005, and ran for four seasons, ending its run on March 25, 2009. The series starred Michael Seater and Ashley Leggat as the two oldest children in a stepfamily. It ended with 70 episodes and one spin-off television film, entitled Vacation with Derek.

Noah Reid, Elizabeth Saunders, Richard Newman

Premiered : November 3, 1997

Prepare for a journey into the heartwarming world of a lovable turtle and his group of woodland friends! As they embark on various adventures and navigate life's lessons together, audiences can't help but be charmed by the timeless wisdom woven throughout simple yet profound tales. This animated series not only entertains but also teaches valuable life skills such as friendship, kindness, perseverance, and problem-solving that resonate with both children and adults alike.

A turtle and his friends discover new things together.

Alexandra Beaton, Victoria Baldesarra, Trevor Tordjman

Premiered : March 8, 2013

Get ready to tap your toes along with this captivating series as it follows a group of talented dancers pursuing their dreams at an elite competitive dance studio! Each character's unique passion for dance fuels the drama that unfolds both on-stage and off; while tackling real-life issues like friendship, jealousy, love, loyalty, triumphs, setbacks, and everything in between. With high-energy performances that'll keep audiences mesmerized from start to finish – it's no surprise this show is a hit among aspiring performers everywhere!

A group of elite dancers strive to win a national-level dance competition.

Dylan Everett, Demetrius Joyette, Hannah Lochner

Premiered : March 31, 2010

Imagine having a guardian angel who's still learning the ropes – that's precisely what happens when two teenagers are paired together in this clever comedy series! With divine intervention gone awry more times than not — these partners stuck together must learn to navigate school life while keeping their supernatural secret under wraps. Filled with laugh-out-loud moments mixed seamlessly with heartwarming life lessons, this lighthearted show will leave viewers entertained and inspired.

An angel-in-training with a devil-may-care attitude is sent to Earth to make a teen popular.

Amanda Arcuri, Jamie Bloch, Chelsea Clark

Premiered : January 4, 2016

It's hard to believe it's school again with this enthralling iteration of the beloved Degrassi franchise. Tackling contemporary issues such as relationships, online privacy, body image, social injustice, mental health, and so much more — this insightful drama presents a realistic portrayal of modern teen life. With relatable characters and compelling storylines that keep audiences emotionally invested throughout each episode; it's no wonder this thought-provoking series has become a timeless classic for generations past and present.

Students encounter common high school issues.

Zoë Belkin, Demetrius Joyette, Vanessa Morgan

Premiered : 2007

Welcome to the fast-paced, cutthroat world of teen journalism! This engaging series follows five aspiring young writers as they juggle school life, friendships, love interests, and their careers at a trendy youth magazine called The Latest Buzz. Each character's unique perspective is explored both in their writing and personal life as they uncover exclusive stories while learning about themselves along the way. For anyone who has ever dreamed of pursuing their passion or simply enjoys a good story – this one's for you!

The Latest Buzz is a Canadian teen sitcom from Decode Entertainment aired on the Family Channel, the series ran from September 1, 2007 to April 19, 2010. This is Family Channel's first original multi-camera sitcom. In this series, a struggling youth magazine, Teen BUZZ, replaces its staff with actual teens. Instead of being in class, five young writers take their last period of the day at the magazine’s office, learning about the fast-paced world of publishing.
